=== Etymology ===
From [[Thomas Bowdler]] who in 1818 published a censored version of [[Shakespeare]], expurgating "...those words and expressions are omitted which cannot with propriety be read aloud in a family."

===Transitive Verb===
#to remove those parts considered offensive, vulgar or adult in nature
#: ''the '''bowdlerized''' version of the text, while free of vulgarity, was also free of flavor''

